[SN]TITLE[SN]
Motorcyclist David Evans killed in Christmas Day M4 crash

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A motorcyclist killed in a crash on the M4 near Newport on Christmas Day has been named.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
David Evans, 49, from Caldicot, Monmouthshire, was pronounced dead at the scene following the eastbound incident between junctions 24 (Coldra) and 25 (Caerleon) at about 18:00 GMT on Friday.
The motorway was closed until Saturday for investigation work to take place.
Gwent Police has asked witnesses to contact them on 101.
